{{Use dmy dates|date=June 2014}} {{Use New Zealand English|date=June 2014}} {{Infobox rugby biography | name = Arthur Hughes | image = | caption = | nickname = | birth_name = Arthur Maitland Hughes | birth_date = {{Birth date|1924|10|11|df=yes}} | birth_place = [[Auckland]], New Zealand | death_place = [[North Shore City|North Shore]], Auckland, New Zealand | death_date = {{Death date and age|2005|06|20|1924|10|11|df=yes}} | ru_position = [[Rugby union positions#Hooker|Hooker]] | height = {{convert|1.78|m|ftin|0|abbr=on}} | weight = {{convert|87|kg|lbs|abbr=on}} | allblackid = 407 | allblackno = 484 | ru_nationalteam = {{nowrap|{{ru|New Zealand|noflag=1}}}} | ru_nationalcaps = 6 | ru_nationalpoints = (0) | ru_nationalyears = 1947–50 | ru_province = [[Auckland Rugby Football Union|Auckland]] | ru_provinceyears = 1947–50 | ru_provincecaps = | ru_provincepoints = | occupation = Managing director | spouse = | children = | relatives = [[Kevin Skinner (rugby union)|Kevin Skinner]] (cousin)<ref name="obit"/> | school = [[Nelson College]]}}
'''Arthur Maitland Hughes''' {{post-nominals|country=NZL|OBE|JP}} (11 October 1924 – 20 June 2005) was a New Zealand [[rugby union]] player. A [[Rugby union positions#Hooker|hooker]], Hughes represented [[Auckland Rugby Football Union|Auckland]] at a provincial level, and was a member of the New Zealand national side, the [[All Blacks]] from 1947 to 1950. Unusually, he was selected for the All Blacks before making his provincial debut. He played seven matches for the All Blacks including six internationals.<ref>{{cite web| url = http://stats.allblacks.com/asp/Profile.asp?ABID=407 |title = Arthur Hughes | last = Luxford | first = Bob | publisher = New Zealand Rugby Museum | accessdate = 14 July 2013}}</ref>
Hughes retired from rugby in 1950 to concentrate on business interests and rose to become managing director of the family liquor firm, Hughes and Cossar. He also served as president of the [[Auckland Racing Club]] and the New Zealand Racing Conference.<ref name="obit">{{cite news | url=http://www.nzherald.co.nz/sport/news/article.cfm?c_id=4&objectid=10332541 | title=Obituary: Arthur Hughes | date=25 June 2005 | work= New Zealand Herald | accessdate=14 July 2013 | first=D.J. | last=Cameron }}</ref>
In the [[1985 Birthday Honours|1985 Queen's Birthday Honours]] he was appointed an [[Officer of the Order of the British Empire]] for services to the racing industry.<ref>{{London Gazette |issue=50155 |date=14 June 1985 |page=2 | supp=y }}</ref>
Two years after his death in 2005, Hughes was inducted into the Waitakere Business Hall of Fame.<ref>{{cite news | title=All Black inducted | date=19 October 2007 | work= Western Leader | page=2 }}</ref>
