'''Factory overhead''', also called '''manufacturing overhead''' or '''work overhead''' or American English '''factory burden''', is the total cost involved in operating all production facilities of a [[manufacturing]] business that cannot be traced directly to a product.<ref>{{Cite book|url=https://www.worldcat.org/oclc/277068142|title=A dictionary of business and management.|date=2009|publisher=Oxford University Press|isbn=9780199234899|edition=5th|location=Oxford [England]|oclc=277068142}}</ref> It generally applies to indirect labor and [[Indirect costs|indirect cost]]. Overhead also includes all costs involved in manufacturing with the exception of the cost of raw materials.

