'''Securities and Exchange Board Of India (Mutual Funds) Regulations, 1996''' is a set of regulations in [[India]] that govern [[mutual fund]]s. It is enforced by the [[Securities and Exchange Board of India]] (SEBI). The regulations have been primarily designed to protect the investors.<ref name="VIJ">{{cite book|author=VIJ|title=Merchant Banking and Financial Services|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=i6T4HSUFzR4C&pg=PA264|accessdate=17 April 2015|publisher=Tata McGraw-Hill Education|isbn=978-1-259-08476-8|page=264}}</ref> This replace an older set of regulations from 1993. SEBI had been regulating the mutual fund market since 1991.<ref name="Machiraju2009">{{cite book|author=H R Machiraju|title=Indian Financial System|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=dv8iQaTm_iAC&pg=PA183|accessdate=17 April 2015|edition=3|date=1 November 2009|publisher=Vikas Publishing House Pvt Ltd|isbn=978-81-259-2401-2|pages=182–183}}</ref>
==Summary== All [[mutual fund]]s must register as [[Trust law|trust]]s under the [[Indian Trusts Act, 1882]]. The firm must set up a separate [[asset management company]] (AMC) to run mutual fund business. The net worth of the parent firm or AMC must be {{currency|50,000,000|INR}}. Mutual funds can be penalised for violating norms. Mutual funds dealing exclusively with the [[money market]] must register with the [[Reserve Bank of India]]. In 1995, private firms were allowed to enter the [[money market in India]] and deal with [[treasury bill]]s, [[commercial paper]]s, [[certificates of deposit]] etc. These are called Money Market Mutual Funds (MMMFs).<ref name="Kothari2010"/>
All other mutual funds must register with the SEBI. Now, there is a self-regulation agency for mutual funds, [[Association of Mutual Funds of India]] (AMFI).<ref name="Kothari2010">{{cite book|author=Rajesh Kothari|title=Financial Services in India: Concept and Application|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=4yGxbcbQNLEC&pg=PA184|accessdate=17 April 2015|date=10 November 2010|publisher=SAGE Publications|isbn=978-81-321-0507-7|page=184}}</ref>
==See also== * [[Securities and Exchange Board of India (Alternative Investment Funds) Regulations, 2012]] * [[Association of Mutual Funds of India]]
