The '''Superior Council for Private Enterprise''' (Consejo Superior de la Empresa Privada, or COSEP) is a leading business chamber in [[Nicaragua]]. As of April 2018, its president is José Adán Aguerri.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Bejarano|first1=Manuel|title=Cosep: solución al INSS no debe afectar competitividad   y la  formalidad|url=https://www.elnuevodiario.com.ni/economia/460764-cosep-solucion-inss-no-debe-afectar-competitividad/|accessdate=23 April 2018|work=El Nuevo Diario|date=April 11, 2018|language=es}}</ref>

COSEP was influential in the proposed 2018 reforms to [[Nicaraguan Social Security Institute|social security in Nicaragua]] and in the [[2018 Nicaraguan protests|resulting protests]].<ref>{{cite news|last1=Gies|first1=Heather|title=At least 10 killed as unrest intensifies in Nicaragua|url=https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2018/04/10-killed-unrest-intensifies-nicaragua-180422060137453.html|accessdate=25 April 2018|work=Al Jazeera|date=22 April 2018}}</ref>

